<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tripp</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-27"><hi rend="italic">August 27,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 85.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to inform you that Mr. Townsend’s
                            dispatch No. 86½, of the 1st instant, inclosing copies of correspondence
                            relative to the refusal of Mr. Schlessing, the U.S. consular agent at
                            Haida, to deliver certain property to the officers of the district
                            court, has been received.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have to say that Mr. Townsend’s course in regard to the matter
                            in question is fully approved by the Department.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>